{"id": "587579", "revid": "27079649", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=587579", "title": "Vorrik's Keystone", "text": "Vorrik's Keystone is one of three keystones that were created by the &lt;a href=\"sethrak\"&gt;sethrak&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Keepers%20%28sethrak%29\"&gt;Keepers&lt;/a&gt; to maintain the barrier around &lt;a href=\"Atul%27Aman\"&gt;Atul'Aman&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Vorrik\"&gt;Vorrik&lt;/a&gt; initially stores the keystone in the topmost chamber of the &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary%20of%20the%20Devoted\"&gt;Sanctuary of the Devoted&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Vol%27dun\"&gt;Vol'dun&lt;/a&gt;, but it's later stolen by the troops of &lt;a href=\"General%20Jakra%27zet\"&gt;General Jakra'zet&lt;/a&gt; along with &lt;a href=\"Sulthis%27%20Keystone\"&gt;Sulthis' Keystone&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "588016", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=588016", "title": "Vorrik's Sanctum", "text": "Vorrik's Sanctum is a cave on the northern slopes of the &lt;a href=\"Crackling%20Ridge\"&gt;Crackling Ridge&lt;/a&gt;, south of the &lt;a href=\"Crater%20of%20Conquerors\"&gt;Crater of Conquerors&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Vol%27dun\"&gt;Vol'dun&lt;/a&gt;. The entrance is located underneath a huge, hollowed-out dead tree. Years ago, the &lt;a href=\"sethrak\"&gt;sethrak&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Vorrik\"&gt;Vorrik&lt;/a&gt; used the cave as his personal sanctum and as a shrine to &lt;a href=\"Sethraliss\"&gt;Sethraliss&lt;/a&gt; where he could meditate, until he was forced to abandon it due to &lt;a href=\"Emperor%20Korthek\"&gt;Korthek&lt;/a&gt;'s betrayal. However, it is currently inhabited by &lt;a href=\"vulpera\"&gt;vulpera&lt;/a&gt; who are fighting the &lt;a href=\"Faithless\"&gt;Faithless&lt;/a&gt; sethrak and rescuing vulpera slaves. Upon discovering this, Vorrik states that, while it's unconventional, he believes Sethraliss would be pleased to see her shrine used to protect innocents in need. He also states that he can still feel the ancient power of Sethraliss in the sanctum, which he takes as a sign that his &lt;a href=\"loa\"&gt;loa&lt;/a&gt; endures."}
