{"id": "366324", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=366324", "title": "To the Skies! (Alliance)", "text": "To the Skies! begins the fourth stage of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder%20storyline\"&gt;Isle of Thunder storyline&lt;/a&gt;, gaining access to the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Vein%20Mine\"&gt;Lightning Vein Mine&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Forges\"&gt;Thunder Forges&lt;/a&gt;. Jaina will only offer this quest from her position on the &lt;a href=\"Violet%20Rise\"&gt;Violet Rise&lt;/a&gt; once enough realm-wide progress has been made, irrespective of the individual player's standing with the &lt;a href=\"Kirin%20Tor%20Offensive\"&gt;Kirin Tor Offensive&lt;/a&gt;.\nMuch like with the previous progression quest, &lt;a href=\"Tear%20Down%20This%20Wall%21%20%28Alliance%29\"&gt;Tear Down This Wall! (Alliance)&lt;/a&gt;, this quest mostly takes place in a single-player scenario, also called \"To the Skies!\". As the scenario can only be completed once, it is documented here and not in a separate article.\nObjectives.\nGain access to the Lightning Vein Mine.\nDescription.\nWe have a plan to halt the Mogu's weaponmaking capabilities, and it involves &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Pterrorwing%20Hatchling%20%28item%29\"&gt;the creature&lt;/a&gt; you recovered from the Zandalari.\nSpeak to me when you're ready to learn more.\nRewards.\nYou will receive: \nProgress.\nIt's time to begin your mission!\nCompletion.\nIncredible work. This presents us with a monumental opportunity.\nNotes.\nOn accept:\nSpeak with her again:\nThis will queue the adventurer for the \"To the Skies!\" single-player scenario.\nStage 1 - Taking Off.\nHead south a few yards to approach the &lt;a href=\"Thunderwing\"&gt;Thunderwing&lt;/a&gt;, Jaina and Vereesa, and the rest of the NPCs at the Violet Rise.\nHop on:\nThe pterrorwing will fly westward through the &lt;a href=\"Diremoor\"&gt;Diremoor&lt;/a&gt; then turn northward to start circling clockwise around the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Vein%20Mine\"&gt;Lightning Vein Mine&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Forges\"&gt;Thunder Forges&lt;/a&gt;.\nStage 2 - Intercepted.\n&lt;a href=\"Zandalari%20Beastcaller\"&gt;Zandalari Beastcaller&lt;/a&gt;s fly up behind the adventurer and will start attacking it with throwing axes. Classes with ranged abilities may stay on their own mount, but the skyscreamers will occasionally get out of range of each other. It will thus likely be easier to Jump! with the bonus action button to the mount of the targeted beastcaller. While circling the mine, the champion is buffed with Thunderous Innervation: \"Killing enemies heals you for 30,000 every 1 sec for 5 sec.\"\nOne beastcaller will spawn, then two, then finally three. Take them all out. The skyscreamer will circle around before reaching the northwestern mine entrance, where &lt;a href=\"Beastmaster%20Horaki\"&gt;Beastmaster Horaki&lt;/a&gt; will shoot the player off its mount!\nStage 3 - Master the Beastmaster.\n&lt;a href=\"Beastmaster%20Horaki\"&gt;Beastmaster Horaki&lt;/a&gt; is a level-90 elite Zandalar troll with nearly three million health. See his article for a full strategy, but get out of the Frost Shot area of effect before he launches the Hail of Arrows. The hails will last for the rest of the encounter, so get just outside of the arrows' area of effect (marked by a red circle) to not waste space.\nFinish him off to start the next stage.\nStage 4 - Into the Mines.\nTaoshi is standing by the cave-in. Speak with her:\nStage 5 - What's Yours is Mine.\nHead into the freshly-opened mine and start killing a path to the southwest through &lt;a href=\"Shan%27ze%20Electrocutioner\"&gt;Shan'ze Electrocutioner&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Shan%27ze%20Slaver\"&gt;Shan'ze Slaver&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"Saurok%20Slave\"&gt;Saurok Slave&lt;/a&gt;s to reach the southern entrance. During this time, Taoshi will chime in randomly:\nFinal Stage - Cover Me.\n&lt;a href=\"Slavemaster%20Shiaxu\"&gt;Slavemaster Shiaxu&lt;/a&gt; is a level-90-elite mogu with 2 million health. See his article for abilities and full tactics. In short, get out of the Capture area of effect, as he will Deadly Kick the same area on his next attack, and get at least 40 yards away from the shackles to break the Chains.\nFinish him off:\nThis completes the \"Take the Forge\" portion of &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder%20%28achievement%29\"&gt;Isle of Thunder (achievement)&lt;/a&gt; as the scenario concludes.\nFinale.\nUse the portal behind Jaina to return to Violet Rise.\nNotes.\nIf you are doing this as a &lt;a href=\"hunter\"&gt;hunter&lt;/a&gt;, you may find the Intercepted! part very hard, heaving good endzone gear will be a boon. Keep in mind that &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Bond%20%28hunter%20talent%29\"&gt;Spirit Bond (hunter talent)&lt;/a&gt; is useless without your pet. Should you want to keep the ability, buy two &lt;a href=\"Tome%20of%20the%20Clear%20Mind\"&gt;Tome of the Clear Mind&lt;/a&gt; and exchage your ability with &lt;a href=\"Exhilaration\"&gt;Exhilaration&lt;/a&gt;. Also, try to stun them with &lt;a href=\"scatter%20Shot\"&gt;scatter Shot&lt;/a&gt; and use a &lt;a href=\"Heavy%20Windwool%20Bandage\"&gt;Heavy Windwool Bandage&lt;/a&gt; to heal."}
{"id": "367542", "revid": "49723770", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=367542", "title": "To the Skies! (Horde)", "text": "Objectives.\nGain access to the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Vein%20Mine\"&gt;Lightning Vein Mine&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nWe can use the &lt;a href=\"pterrorwing\"&gt;pterrorwing&lt;/a&gt; that you found to strike a decisive blow against the &lt;a href=\"mogu\"&gt;mogu&lt;/a&gt;. Their mining operation is vulnerable to attack from the air, and your pterrorwing is the only beast we have capable of flying out there. Let me know when you are ready!\nRewards.\nYou will receive: \nProgress.\nIt's time to begin your mission!\nCompletion.\nIncredible work. This presents us with a monumental opportunity.\nNotes.\nOn accept:\nSpeak with him again:\nThis will queue the adventurer for the \"To the Skies!\" single-player scenario.\nStage 1 - Taking Off.\nHead south a few yards to approach the &lt;a href=\"Thunderwing\"&gt;Thunderwing&lt;/a&gt;, and Elsia.\nHop on:\nThe pterrorwing will fly westward through the &lt;a href=\"Diremoor\"&gt;Diremoor&lt;/a&gt; then turn northward to start circling clockwise around the &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Vein%20Mine\"&gt;Lightning Vein Mine&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Forges\"&gt;Thunder Forges&lt;/a&gt;.\nStage 2 - Intercepted.\n&lt;a href=\"Zandalari%20Beastcaller\"&gt;Zandalari Beastcaller&lt;/a&gt;s fly up behind the adventurer and will start attacking it with throwing axes. Classes with ranged abilities may stay on their own mount, but the skyscreamers will occasionally get out of range of each other. It will thus likely be easier to Jump! with the bonus action button to the mount of the targeted beastcaller. While circling the mine, the champion is buffed with Thunderous Innervation: \"Killing enemies heals you for 30,000 every 1 sec for 5 sec.\"\nOne beastcaller will spawn, then two, then finally three. Take them all out. The skyscreamer will circle around before reaching the northwestern mine entrance, where &lt;a href=\"Beastmaster%20Horaki\"&gt;Beastmaster Horaki&lt;/a&gt; will shoot the player off its mount!\nStage 3 - Master the Beastmaster.\n&lt;a href=\"Beastmaster%20Horaki\"&gt;Beastmaster Horaki&lt;/a&gt; is a level-90 elite Zandalar troll with nearly three million health. See his article for a full strategy, but get out of the Frost Shot area of effect before he launches the Hail of Arrows. The hails will last for the rest of the encounter, so get just outside of the arrows' area of effect (marked by a red circle) to not waste space.\nFinish him off to start the next stage.\nStage 4 - Into the Mines.\nTaoshi is standing by the cave-in. Speak with her:\nStage 5 - What's Yours is Mine.\nHead into the freshly-opened mine and start killing a path to the southwest through &lt;a href=\"Shan%27ze%20Electrocutioner\"&gt;Shan'ze Electrocutioner&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Shan%27ze%20Slaver\"&gt;Shan'ze Slaver&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"Saurok%20Slave\"&gt;Saurok Slave&lt;/a&gt;s to reach the southern entrance. During this time, Taoshi will chime in randomly:\nFinal Stage - Cover Me.\n&lt;a href=\"Slavemaster%20Shiaxu\"&gt;Slavemaster Shiaxu&lt;/a&gt; is a level-90-elite mogu with 2 million health. See his article for abilities and full tactics. In short, get out of the Capture area of effect, as he will Deadly Kick the same area on his next attack, and get at least 40 yards away from the shackles to break the Chains.\nFinish him off:\nThis completes the \"Take the Forge\" portion of &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder%20%28achievement%29\"&gt;Isle of Thunder (achievement)&lt;/a&gt; as the scenario concludes.\nFinale.\nUse the portal behind Lor'themar to return to Dawnseeker Promontory."}
