{"id": "565646", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=565646", "title": "Toki, Time-Tinker", "text": "Toki, Time-Tinker is a &lt;a href=\"gnome\"&gt;gnome&lt;/a&gt; featured in the \"\" expansion for \"&lt;a href=\"Hearthstone%20%28game%29\"&gt;Hearthstone&lt;/a&gt;\". A friend of &lt;a href=\"Chronormu\"&gt;Chronormu&lt;/a&gt;, Toki is a &lt;a href=\"time%20travel\"&gt;time travel&lt;/a&gt;er who tinkers with bending &lt;a href=\"time\"&gt;time&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"alternate%20timeline\"&gt;alternate timeline&lt;/a&gt;s and is able to create time portals to call for help from of the past. Toki represents the \"Time-Tinker\" class in the single-player experience.\nBackground.\nTwo conflicting reports about Toki have recently come to light. One describes a powerful young mage who posses an uncanny talent for time magic, who, unusually, often channels her power through arcane devices of her own invention rather than casting spells. Her unflappable determination and willingness to take inconceivable risks makes her a dangerously effective hunter who is somehow always exactly where she needs to be at the exact right moment, and chance events tend to go her way far more often than they should. Unfortunately, Toki's extreme talent is paired with a blithe disregard for the consequences her magics might cause to the fabric of time. She displays a similar cheerful apathy toward &lt;a href=\"Gilneas%20peninsula\"&gt;Gilneas&lt;/a&gt; and the curse of the Witchwood, appearing solely interested in stopping &lt;a href=\"Hagatha%20the%20Witch\"&gt;Hagatha the Witch&lt;/a&gt; from affecting an event in her own future.\nThe other report describes a fiendishly powerful, scarred, and grizzled &lt;a href=\"archmage\"&gt;archmage&lt;/a&gt; with an incredible innate control over time magic. There have been frequent sightings of in Gilneas of late, though only for moments at a time. Witnesses have noted that her form flickers in and out of existence, as if she can't maintain her presence in this timeline for long, and they describe her as seemingly being haunted, crazed, or obsessed. Bizarrely, she has been showing citizens pictures of herself and asking them if they have \"seen this gnome\". She displays a grim disregard for Gilneas and the curse of the Witchwood, appearing solely interested in someone in this city from affecting an event in her own future.\nBoth of these reports arrived at exactly the same time, and the agent who delivered them disavowed any knowledge of writing either report."}
