{"id": "49206", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49206", "title": "Silverwind Refuge", "text": "Silverwind Refuge is located in south-central &lt;a href=\"Ashenvale\"&gt;Ashenvale&lt;/a&gt;, just north of &lt;a href=\"Mystral%20Lake\"&gt;Mystral Lake&lt;/a&gt; and directly south of the &lt;a href=\"Remains%20of%20Iris%20Lake\"&gt;Remains of Iris Lake&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Peak\"&gt;Thunder Peak&lt;/a&gt;. It is a &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; outpost with a &lt;a href=\"flight%20master\"&gt;flight master&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"innkeeper\"&gt;innkeeper&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"quest%20giver\"&gt;quest giver&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"stable%20master\"&gt;stable master&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"vendor\"&gt;vendor&lt;/a&gt;s. The corpses of some of the previous inhabitants still lie on the ground around the outpost. The main building that functions as an &lt;a href=\"inn\"&gt;inn&lt;/a&gt; has a beautiful view on the lake that borders it. \nThe quest &lt;a href=\"We%27re%20Here%20to%20Do%20One%20Thing%2C%20Maybe%20Two...\"&gt;We're Here to Do One Thing, Maybe Two...&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Guard%20Aldo%20Rockrain\"&gt;Blood Guard Aldo Rockrain&lt;/a&gt; begins the Horde quest line for Stonetalon Mountains.\nHistory.\nWorld of Warcraft.\nPrior to the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt; Silverwind Refuge was a &lt;a href=\"Night%20elf\"&gt;night elven&lt;/a&gt; settlement that contained an &lt;a href=\"alchemy%20trainer\"&gt;alchemy trainer&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"herbalism%20trainer\"&gt;herbalism trainer&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"hunter%20trainer\"&gt;hunter trainer&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"pet%20trainer\"&gt;pet trainer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"quest%20giver\"&gt;quest giver&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"skinning%20trainer\"&gt;skinning trainer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"vendor\"&gt;vendor&lt;/a&gt;s. It was under the protection of an elite guard known as the &lt;a href=\"Sentinel\"&gt;Sentinel&lt;/a&gt;s and their army of &lt;a href=\"water%20elemental\"&gt;water elemental&lt;/a&gt;s. It was a major outpost in Ashenvale along with Astranaar, which once lived up to its name\u2014a welcoming place with a comparatively luxurious inn.\nCataclysm.\nThe night elves thought Silverwind to be impenetrable, with its heavy defenses and their army of water elementals. However, during the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; attack, by the time of the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;, one of their &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s was able to summon a twisted elemental designed to send the night elven water elementals into a chaotic rage. With the enraged elementals attacking all they saw before them, victory was assured for the Horde.\nThe surviving night elves fled to the nearby &lt;a href=\"Stardust%20Spire\"&gt;Stardust Spire&lt;/a&gt; and vowed revenge for the loss of the outpost. The orcs had slaughtered Sentinels and civilians alike, and they hunted down those who tried to flee, letting their bodies rot in the road as a brutal warning to anyone who would try to retake Silverwind Refuge. The orcs proceed to use the outpost as a starting point for their push into the surrounding regions. Not long after, the Horde set up logging operations in the surrounding area and begun to clear the forest.\nAt some point after the events of the Cataclysm, a small army of Sentinels led by &lt;a href=\"Anaris%20Windwood\"&gt;Anaris Windwood&lt;/a&gt; reclaimed Silverwind from the Horde.\nBattle for Azeroth.\nBy the time of the &lt;a href=\"War%20of%20the%20Thorns\"&gt;War of the Thorns&lt;/a&gt;, Silverwind Refuge was considered a night elven outpost and a center of Sentinel's presence. It would later fall to the Horde while they marched through Ashenvale.\nSome time later after the Burning of Teldrassil, Sentinels from &lt;a href=\"Stardust%20Spire\"&gt;Stardust Spire&lt;/a&gt; launched an assault to retake Silverwind Refuge from the Horde. There, they faced off &lt;a href=\"Valusha\"&gt;Valusha&lt;/a&gt;."}
