{"id": "558999", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=558999", "title": "Vok'fon", "text": "Vok'fon is a &lt;a href=\"jungle%20troll\"&gt;jungle troll&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Primal%20%28occupation%29\"&gt;primal&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;. He is a son of &lt;a href=\"Master%20Vornal\"&gt;Master Vornal&lt;/a&gt; and an outcast from the &lt;a href=\"Darkspear%20tribe\"&gt;Darkspear tribe&lt;/a&gt; because he openly spoke against the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; that they would make the Darkspears weak. He is described as a barbaric &lt;a href=\"warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt;. \nHe and his group of bandits once attacked &lt;a href=\"Brann%20Bronzebeard\"&gt;Brann Bronzebeard&lt;/a&gt; and his group, leaving Brann as the only survivor and taking him as prisoner. As the dwarf fought as a true warrior, the troll treated him with respect and honor. During the following days, sharing conversations with them, Brann learned much about the &lt;a href=\"troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; races, history and organizations from Vok'fon and his comrades. After three weeks of traveling, the troll considered him an equal and eventually set him free."}
