{"id": "75771", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=75771", "title": "Han'al", "text": "Han'al was a &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Kirin%20Tor\"&gt;Kirin Tor&lt;/a&gt; and their Master Lorekeeper. He had written and compiled a tome of great and dangerous knowledge which he called \"&lt;a href=\"Magic%20%26amp%3B%20Mayhem\"&gt;Magic &amp; Mayhem&lt;/a&gt;\". The book held paths to unknown power, containing lore about magic, classes, magical items, weapons, and constructs. He warned people to be careful not to allow the book to lead them to feelings that the world was theirs to conquer. He warned that such delusions would lead only to ruin."}
{"id": "544428", "revid": "40890366", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=544428", "title": "Han'jin", "text": "Han'jin is an &lt;a href=\"ice%20troll\"&gt;ice troll&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Drakkari%20tribe\"&gt;Drakkari tribe&lt;/a&gt; who has been uniting camps of hunting parties in the &lt;a href=\"Borean%20Tundra\"&gt;Borean Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. They are currently building a more permanent base while inviting other camps to join them. If Han'jin keeps the hunters united, he will become the ruler of a small town, and the Drakkari will become a major threat to the &lt;a href=\"tuskarr\"&gt;tuskarr&lt;/a&gt; and anyone else roaming the Borean Tundra."}
